        content: "1. A computer-implemented method for simultaneous cardiovascular and psychological biomarker extraction from facial video comprising: capturing a facial video sequence of a user using a consumer smartphone camera for a duration of between fifteen and sixty seconds; processing the captured video through a cardiovascular extraction pipeline that applies remote photoplethysmography to detect blood volume pulse signals from facial skin regions and derives therefrom at least blood pressure estimates, heart rate, and heart rate variability; simultaneously processing the same captured video through a psychological extraction pipeline that analyzes facial action unit activations, micro-expression occurrences, skin pallor, periorbital indicators, blink patterns, and gaze stability to derive therefrom at least an emotional valence score, an anxiety indicator, and a depression risk indicator; correlating outputs from the cardiovascular and psychological pipelines through a compound biomarker fusion layer that identifies health indicators dependent on the interaction between cardiovascular and psychological states; and storing the extracted biomarkers in a longitudinal trajectory database for trend analysis across multiple capture sessions.\n\n2. The method of claim 1, wherein the cardiovascular extraction pipeline performs region of interest detection to identify facial skin regions excluding hair, eyes, eyebrows, lips, and facial hair, decomposes each region into color channels, applies independent component analysis to isolate the cardiac-synchronous blood volume pulse component, and estimates pulse transit time from temporal offsets between blood volume pulse arrival at spatially separated facial regions.\n\n3. The method of claim 1, wherein the psychological extraction pipeline detects micro-expressions lasting less than five hundred milliseconds by identifying frame-by-frame deviations in facial action unit activation sequences from the user's voluntary expression pattern established during a neutral baseline period.\n\n4. The method of claim 1, wherein the compound biomarker fusion layer generates lifecycle-phase-specific compound indicators comprising: a preeclampsia anxiety compound alert when elevated blood pressure co-occurs with elevated anxiety indicators during a pregnancy lifecycle phase; a postpartum depression compound indicator when flattened emotional valence co-occurs with elevated fatigue indicators during a postpartum lifecycle phase; and a perimenopause cardiovascular mood compound pattern when blood pressure variability increase co-occurs with mood volatility increase during a perimenopause lifecycle phase.\n\n5. The method of claim 1, further comprising a guided capture module that provides real-time feedback to the user on face positioning, lighting adequacy, and stillness, and that prompts a standardized sequence of neutral baseline maintenance followed by specified facial movements to capture dynamic expression range.\n\n6. The method of claim 1, wherein the depression risk indicator is calibrated against Edinburgh Postnatal Depression Scale equivalence scores using a validated mapping function derived from concurrent administration of the EPDS questionnaire and facial video capture in a clinical training cohort.\n\n7. The method of claim 1, wherein the longitudinal trajectory database maintains dual-biomarker trajectories enabling trend analysis at short-term, medium-term, and long-term time horizons, with clinical threshold alerting that evaluates both absolute biomarker values and trajectory slope to distinguish acute deviations from progressive trends.\n\n8. A dual-purpose biometric monitoring system for reproductive health comprising: a video capture module configured to record facial video from a smartphone front-facing camera with guided positioning and lighting assessment; a cardiovascular analysis engine configured to extract blood pressure estimates, heart rate, heart rate variability, and oxygen saturation from remote photoplethysmography analysis of the captured facial video; a psychological analysis engine configured to extract emotional valence, arousal, anxiety indicators, depression risk indicators, fatigue indicators, and cognitive load estimates from facial action unit analysis, micro-expression detection, skin pallor analysis, periorbital analysis, blink pattern analysis, and gaze stability analysis of the same captured facial video; a fusion engine configured to generate compound biomarker indicators from correlated cardiovascular and psychological outputs; and a trajectory engine configured to maintain longitudinal dual-biomarker histories and generate clinical alerts based on absolute values and trend slopes.\n\n9. The system of claim 8, wherein the psychological analysis engine operates transparently during a user-initiated cardiovascular check, requiring no additional user action, input, or awareness beyond the initial informed consent for comprehensive health monitoring, thereby functioning as a passive mental health screening mechanism embedded within routine cardiovascular monitoring.\n\n10. The system of claim 8, wherein the fusion engine detects discordant patterns where cardiovascular and psychological signals diverge unexpectedly, including elevated blood pressure with abnormally low anxiety indicators indicative of emotional suppression, and generates differential clinical follow-up recommendations based on concordance or discordance classification.\n\n11. The system of claim 8, further comprising a calibration module that establishes user-specific mapping between pulse transit time measurements and absolute blood pressure values using a reference measurement from a validated blood pressure monitor, with recalibration triggering when drift detection identifies progressive divergence between rPPG-derived and expected pressure values.\n\n12. The system of claim 8, wherein the trajectory engine interfaces with a lifecycle transition detection system and contributes dual-biomarker trajectory patterns as evidence inputs to lifecycle phase transition algorithms, enabling routine face scan sessions to support lifecycle monitoring without additional user burden.\n\n13. A method for passive mental health screening in reproductive health monitoring comprising: presenting a user with a facial scan interface framed as a cardiovascular health check; capturing facial video while providing the user with real-time cardiovascular feedback including estimated blood pressure and heart rate; simultaneously and transparently analyzing the captured facial video for psychological biomarkers including depression risk indicators, anxiety indicators, and fatigue indicators without displaying psychological assessment results in real-time; storing psychological biomarker results in a longitudinal trajectory database; evaluating psychological biomarker trajectories against clinical threshold criteria; and when trajectory criteria indicate elevated mental health risk, generating a clinical alert routed to the user's care team for follow-up action, wherein the user's engagement with routine cardiovascular monitoring serves as the sole required user action for ongoing mental health screening.\n\n14. The method of claim 13, wherein the psychological biomarker trajectory evaluation applies lifecycle-phase-specific threshold criteria, with postpartum-phase thresholds calibrated for postpartum depression detection sensitivity, perimenopause-phase thresholds calibrated for perimenopause-associated mood disorder detection, and general-phase thresholds calibrated for population-baseline mental health screening.\n\n15. The method of claim 13, further comprising integrating the extracted cardiovascular and psychological biomarkers with continuous wearable monitoring data including basal body temperature, heart rate variability from wearable sensors, and sleep architecture metrics to generate a multi-modal health assessment that combines face-scan-derived biomarkers with continuously monitored physiological data for enhanced clinical accuracy.\n\n16. The method of claim 13, wherein the clinical alert generation considers both individual biomarker trajectories and compound indicators derived from the correlation of cardiovascular and psychological biomarker streams, prioritizing compound indicators that have demonstrated higher predictive validity for the user's current lifecycle phase."
