        content: "A system and method for simultaneously extracting cardiovascular and psychological biomarkers from a single facial video capture session using a consumer smartphone camera. The system applies remote photoplethysmography to derive blood pressure estimates, heart rate, heart rate variability, and oxygen saturation from facial skin color variations, while simultaneously analyzing facial action units, micro-expressions, skin pallor, periorbital indicators, blink patterns, and gaze stability to derive emotional valence, anxiety indicators, depression risk indicators, and fatigue indicators. A compound biomarker fusion layer correlates cardiovascular and psychological outputs to identify lifecycle-phase-specific compound health indicators including preeclampsia-anxiety patterns, postpartum depression compound indicators, and perimenopause cardiovascular-mood patterns. A longitudinal trajectory engine maintains dual-biomarker histories enabling trend-based clinical alerting. The system enables passive mental health screening embedded within routine cardiovascular monitoring, reducing user burden and overcoming stigma barriers to mental health assessment in reproductive health populations."
