        title: "ABSTRACT",
        content: "A system and method for coordinated reproductive health optimization across both partners in a conception-seeking couple. The system maintains independent health profiles for each partner with separate data ingestion pipelines: the female partner's profile receives continuous wearable data including basal body temperature, heart rate variability, sleep architecture, and glucose monitoring, while the male partner's profile receives periodic semen analysis results and daily lifestyle factor tracking. A shared reproductive outcome model computes joint conception probability incorporating compensatory, complementary, and timing interaction effects between partners' contributions. A joint optimization algorithm recalculates both partners' intervention protocols whenever either partner's data changes, identifying the binding constraint across both partners and distributing intervention intensity to maximize marginal improvement in joint conception probability subject to adherence capacity constraints and biological timeline alignment. A privacy-preserving data sharing layer provides configurable visibility tiers between partners. An AI care team generates coordinated recommendations with awareness of both partners' health contexts while respecting privacy boundaries. The system enables scenarios where improvement in one partner's data triggers protocol priority rebalancing for the other partner, producing joint optimization outcomes unavailable from independent single-partner fertility tools."
