        title: "SUMMARY OF THE INVENTION",
        content: "The present invention provides an automated lifecycle transition system for reproductive health management that detects physiological state changes through continuous wearable monitoring and automatically reconfigures the health management platform in response. The system supports eight primary lifecycle transitions: menarche preparation to menstrual cycle establishment, menstrual monitoring to condition-specific management such as PCOS or endometriosis, menstrual monitoring to active fertility optimization, fertility optimization to pregnancy, pregnancy to postpartum recovery, postpartum recovery to menstrual monitoring or fertility optimization, menstrual monitoring to perimenopause, and perimenopause to post-menopause.\n\nEach transition is triggered by physiological state detection rather than manual user selection. The system recognizes that the user's physiology has changed and automatically adapts the monitoring experience. Upon transition detection, the system reconfigures five platform dimensions: scoring algorithm parameters including factor categories, weights, and thresholds are reconfigured for the new lifecycle phase, monitoring protocols including measurement frequency, signal categories, and escalation sensitivity are adjusted, care team behavior including which AI agents are active, their communication style, and their clinical focus areas are adapted, intervention strategies including supplement protocols, nutritional recommendations, and lifestyle guidance are modified, and content delivery including educational materials, community features, and notification patterns are updated.\n\nCritically, all transitions preserve complete longitudinal data continuity. When a woman transitions from fertility optimization to pregnancy, her entire physiological history including cycle patterns, intervention response data, baseline values, and care team context carries forward. The pregnancy monitoring system does not start from scratch but begins with deep knowledge of the individual's physiology, enabling personalized thresholds and more accurate risk assessment from the first day of pregnancy monitoring."
