        title: "ABSTRACT",
        content: "A system and method for automated integration of at-home diagnostic laboratory results with continuous physiological monitoring data from wearable devices in the context of reproductive health management. The system receives laboratory results through electronic data interchange, direct API integration, or optical character recognition, normalizes them using a comprehensive analyte ontology with lifecycle-phase-adjusted reference ranges, and contextualizes each result against the user's individual historical trajectory and correlated continuous monitoring data streams. An AI care team generates personalized multi-layered plain-language interpretations explaining each result in the context of the user's personal physiological trajectory rather than solely against population reference ranges. A protocol adjustment engine computes specific care modifications including supplement formulation changes with dosage calculations based on the user's individual absorption profile, nutritional guidance updates, monitoring parameter adjustments, and clinical escalation recommendations. A safety verification layer validates all proposed adjustments against interaction databases, dosage limits, and lifecycle-phase-specific contraindication criteria. The system enables laboratory results to directly influence all aspects of the user's care experience, from supplement protocols through AI care conversations to lifecycle phase transition detection, closing the gap between clinical measurement and actionable care protocol adjustment that exists in current laboratory result delivery systems."
